Arthroscopic management of transchondral talar-dome fractures (osteochondritis dissecans) and anterior impingement lesions of the ankle joint.
 Transchondral talar-dome fractures can be disabling conditions requiring surgical management.
 Arthroscopic surgery of the ankle offers a means of correcting these problems with low morbidity.
 A technique for performing this surgery utilizing a new noninvasive distraction device is reviewed in this article.
